column1: # USGS High Plains Water-Level Monitoring Study
# For questions regarding this data, please email vlmcguir@usgs.gov
# This file consists of tab-separated columns of data for a list of sites.
# The following selected columns are included in this file:

column4: State, the 2-digit Federal Information Processing Standards (FIPS) numeric code for the State in which the site is located
County, the 3-digit FIPS numeric code for the county in which the site is located
The 5 character agency code and 15-digit U.S. Geological Survey (USGS) site identification number (station number).

column5: The agency code is the source agency for site information.

column4: Other identification code for well (for example, the TWDB identifier)
Site name, generally the site legal description
Latitude in degrees, minutes, seconds (DDMMSS.SS) as stored in the source database (KGS, TWDB, or USGS)
Longitude in degrees, minutes, seconds (DDDMMSS.SS) as stored in the source database (KGS, TWDB, or USGS)
Horizontal datum for latitude and longitude in degrees, minutes, seconds. The horizontal datum is not available for TWDB wells and is assumed to be NAD27
Latitude in decimal degrees, datum NAD83
Longitude in decimal degrees, datum NAD83
Latitude/longitude accuracy, the 1 digit code, accuracy to:
Method for determining Latitude/longitude, by:
Altitude of land surface, in feet above National Geodetic Vertical Datum of 1929
Well depth, in feet below land surface (missing value = -999)
Number of screened intervals in well (missing value = -99)
Total screened length of well, in feet (missing value = -999)
Depth to top of shallowest screen, in feet below land surface (missing value = -999)
Depth to bottom of deepest screen, in feet below land surface (missing value = -999)
Water-level measurement date, (YYYYMMDD)
Water-level measurement time, if available, (xx:xx in 24 hour time)
Water level below land surface, in feet, water levels are generally accurate to the hundredth place
